Requirements:
Installation of Rails 3 environment. This can be done by:
sudo apt-get install rails
sudo apt-get install gems
gem install rails

Installation of ccenv:
Download this environment into the directory in which you like it
git clone git@github.com:wassinki/ccenv.git

Now do:
cd ccenv
bundle install


Now the environment should work. Optionally you can do 
ln script/ccenv ~/bin/ccenv

The cucumber envrinoment can be run using the command
ccenv [-p env] [-t tag] [-n name] [NO_EXTERNAL_SERVER=true] <feature directories>
-p: environment [selenium, mechanize(default)]
-t: tags
-n: feature names

Additionally, you can use all cucumber options






This environment is created using the following commands:

rails new ccenv
cd ccenv
rails plugin install git@github.com:wassinki/cucumber_environment.git

rails g cucumber_environment cucumber
bundle install

echo "Test the ccenv with the command ruby ./script/ccenv vendor/plugins/cucumber_environment/test/features/"
ruby ./script/ccenv vendor/plugins/cucumber_environment/test/features/

